Given it is the start of a new year and there are new people in this community, I thought I would share a few facts and truths. 

1) I post daily - typically a highlight in my day, I don’t use filters but will search out the best lighting I can. I love to engage but also try to limit my exposure on social media to a reasonable amount. 

2) My focus is #family #finances #fitness and #fun. Not always in that order. Some of my family members embrace Instagram and others tolerate me. 🙃 I respect that. 

3) When I share goals and challenges I’m hoping this might encouraged you to set your goals and challenges for yourself. My hope is that together we grow at our own pace as a community. 

4) I have been accused of being “unbelievably extra” and well, I can’t argue with that. In fact, I actually embrace it. I am a confident person and I can be a vulnerable one and I’m ok with being both. 
.
If this of any interest to you at all - thank you for following along. If it isn’t - I totally get that as well. 
.

I’m excited for 2023 and can’t wait to say “yes” to new opportunities, adventures and lifestyle decisions and yup I will post all about. ❤️ I really hope you come along and btw I do try to read every comment 🙏😊
.

Feeling the pressure to keep up with those around us is a trap that leads to financial strain and stress. Remember, living within your means and finding financial stability is what truly matters. Here are some tips for financially living within your means:

💰Make a budget: Track your income and expenses to see where your money is going and make adjustments as needed.

🛍️Prioritize spending: Identify what is important to you and allocate your resources accordingly.

⚠️Avoid debt: Try to pay off debt as quickly as possible and avoid taking on new debt, if possible.

💸Save for the future: Build an emergency fund and save for long-term goals, such as retirement.

📈Be mindful of lifestyle inflation: Don't let your spending increase as your income does.

Embrace your unique journey and focus on creating a life that brings you joy and peace of mind, not just temporary material possessions.

What we have been told by the doctors here at Sick Kids, is that she has a very rare liver cancer called Hepatoblastoma.
